title.narrative: Strengthened child protection legal, policy and regulatory frameworks

description.narrative: Child protection legal, policy and regulatory frameworks were strengthened with the launch of the NIVAC strategy. The strategy complements the child protection mapping review where cumulatively UNICEF supported the implementation of 39/69 recommendations. UNICEF supported the increase of the MOSD social workforce to a total of 35 active CP Counsellors ensuring protection support to 2,386 children (468 girls and 1918 boys) in the WB. The first 20 community male mediators were trained to mediate cases of children in conflict with the law. The CP AoR has facilitated child protection service provision to 22,566 children (11,893 girls and 10,673 boys). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
